Detailed Description

This class template is a collection of functions from Vector, ObjVector and VoidVector.

(PointerVector is not included since that is never used.)

uint32 TemplateVector::binarySearch (  const ElementType  keyElm,
uint32  start = 0,
uint32  stop = MAX_UINT32
)  const [inline]
 

Performs a binarysearch for an element with the same key as the parameter.

The vector has to be sorted when using this function. If it's not sorted -- use the linearSerach()-method.

Parameters:
keyElm The value to search for.
start Optional parameter, indicating the index of the first element to search among. Default value is 0.
stop Optional parameter, indicating the index of the last element to search among. Default value is indexToUse-1.
Returns:
Offset in array to an element with key == key. InvalidElement is returned if no such element in array.
